The paper deals with the problem of finding a "best" deterministic query answer to a query over a probabilistic database, which is a fundamental problem in the field of probabilistic databases. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also proposes a notion of consensus world and considers various types of queries including SPJ queries, Topk queries, group-by aggregate queries, and clustering, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper provides polynomial time optimal or approximation algorithms for computing the consensus answers for different distance metrics, which is a topic in the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
